<-------------------> this all are very important topics <---------------------------->

1. Process vs Object Oriented
2. Instance Variables and Methods
3. Declaring and Using Objects
4. Class vs Object
5. This & Static Keyword
6. Constructors & Code Blocks
7. Stack vs Heap Memory
8. Primitive vs Reference Types
9. Variable Scopes
10.Garbage Collection & Finalize

<---------------------------------Explaination---------------------------------------->

1. Process vs Object Oriented :
-> process ko hamm procedural bhi bolte hai isme hamar pura data ek function ke andar hota
hai matlab ki hamara pura data function ke andar hi ghumega.
-> for example :- ham ek banking system bana rhae hai to procesdural me important hai
ki kaam kya kya karna hai matlab sirf withdraw , deposit and transfer bass procedural
me itna hi socha jayega procedural me ham direct kaam soach te hai ki hamko kya kya
karna hoga uss hisab se ham apna function lhikte hai.
-> object oriented me hamara pura data objects ke andar rheta hai and hamar pura data
classes ya to object ke ass pass ghumta hai.
-> for example :- ham ek banking system bana rhae hai to object oriented hame ye soche
nge phele ki isme objects kya kya hai and whai objects ke related hamara data hoga
banking system me hamare objects honge customer , money , account.
customer:- ye paisa deposite , withdraw , transfer karshakta hai etc.
money :- isme ham ye lhik shakte hai ki paisa kitne baje depsoite hua ya to kitne baje
paisa nikla pura paise ka hisab rhakega ye object.
account :- isme ham ye lhik shakte hai ki hamara account kab create hu account ka malik
kon hai account ke kitna transaction hua and bhot kuch.
-> iske andar ham apne data ka bheaviour bhi change kar shakte hai.
-> hame problem milte to shabse phele soach na hai ki isme objects konse konse hai
ya actor kon kon hai problem question me.

2. Instance Variables and Methods
-> shamjo sirf jo bhi niche lhika raha hu

class Cat
properties :- four legs , mustache,fluffy , tail , teeth , do kan.
methods :- lie , mew , jump , scratch.
-> ye jo properties hai isiko ham bolte hai instance variables
and methods bolte hai instance methods

class Car
attributes :- fuel , maxspeed.
methods :- refule() , getfuel() , setSpeed() , getSpeed().
-> attributes ko ham properties bhi bolte hai.

3. Declaring and Using Objects
-> Car myCar = new Car();
-> ye uppar hamne banya hai ek object phela wala jo Car hai wo hamara class name hai .
-> myCar hamara refrence hai jisko ham variable bolte the.
-> new ki madat se ham ek object bana pa rahe hai and object ka name hai Car() and
iska ham addres dal denge myCar ke andar .
-> jab ham koi naya object banate hai to uske shat ek address bhi create hojata hai
jisko haam refrence ke andar pass karte hai .
-> jab bhi hamko mycar() ka object chaiye hoga to ham myCar se lelenge simple.
-> heap ke andar hamare object ki memory allocate hai .
-> Car() isko ham constructor bh bolte hai.
-> me iske behaviour ko acces kar shakta hu . se myCar.addFuel();

4. Class vs Object
-> class ka matlab hota hai sirf blueprint wo accutal me koi memory nhai leta class
hame sirf ye bata hai ki to tum uski madat se kya bana shakte ho or kaise bana shakte ho .
-> object ki maddat se ham wo cizz actual me banate hai.
-> heap ke andar ham apni object ki memory ko allocate karte hai.

5. This & Static Keyword
->this ka matlab hota hai apna current object.
-> static wale method ke andar hame direct instance variable ko nhai lhik shakte hai
hame object ke shaat hi lhik na hoga.
-> static hamesa class ke je ass pass rheta hai .
-> static se jo bhi ham method bana te hai usko hame direct class ke shaat call karna hoga
or jha ham call kar rhae honge wo method bhi static hona chaiye.


